(1) The Civil Service Commission shall appoint as public officers in the ministry responsible for Mines, the— (a) Director of Geological Survey; (b) Director of Artisanal, Small Scale Mining and Value Addition; (c) Director of Large-Scale Mining and Mineral Investment Promotion; and (d) such other public officers as may be necessary for the proper administration of this Act.
